      "title": "Perceived exertion: a note on history and methods",
      "abstract": "ABSTRACTEarly studies of subjective force estimates for short-time work on a bicycle ergometer are reviewed. Results showed that perceived pedal resistance followed a positively accelerating function with an exponent of 1.6. A model for inter-individunl comparisons using subjective range as a frame"
